{"id":"969496279507778512","name":"LCH","lastUpdateDate":"2021-04-29T07:13:15.709Z","publisherHandle":"zisest","publisherImage":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/578d32edeabc7d98108814399498c19b?size=240&default=https%3A%2F%2Fs3-alpha.figma.com%2Fstatic%2Fuser_n_v2.png","publisherId":"2368961","publisherName":"Nikita Antonov","description":"<p>A simple color picker that utilizes LCH color space.</p><p><br></p><ul><li>Pick color by adjusting lightness, chroma, hue and alpha levels;</li><li>Use it in your designs;</li><li>Export it to CSS&nbsp;<code>lch()</code>&nbsp;notation (see&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/css-color-4/#specifying-lab-lch\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">CSS Color Spec 4</a>) or the closest&nbsp;<code>rgb()</code>&nbsp;alternative</li></ul><p><br></p><p>Source code is available at <a href=\"https://github.com/zisest/figma-lch-plugin\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">GitHub</a>. The plugin is heavily based on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://lea.verou.me/\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Lea Verou</a>'s picker available at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://css.land/lch/\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">css.land/lch/</a>. Conversion logic is by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://svgees.us/\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Chris Lilley</a>.</p>","url":"https://www.figma.com/community/plugin/969496279507778512","iconUrl":"https://www.figma.com/community/plugin/969496279507778512/icon","thumbnailUrl":"https://www.figma.com/community/plugin/969496279507778512/thumbnail"}
